<TITLE> Police detain Rajshahi city Jamaat chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)  Police arrested Rajshahi metropolitan Jamaat-e-Islami chief Maulana Ataur Rahman on Thursday morning in connection with Tuesday's killing of a Rajshahi University student. Ataur was arrested in front of the city's Loknath School at around 10:30am on charges of attacks and vandalizing in the university campus and abetting the killing of Faruk Hossain, said Jashim Uddin, officer-in-charge of Boalia Model Police Station. Faruk Hossain was killed and scores of others were injured in fierce clashes between cadres of Bangladesh Chhatra League and Islami Chhatra Shibir in the early hours of Tuesday. Motihar police chief Tofazzal Hossain said they had detained four Shibir leaders on Wednesday night, but did not reveal their identity. Two cases were filed on Wednesday against hundreds of Shibir activists while dozens were detained in connection with the campus violence. Police on Wednesday took 28 Shibir activists into custody for quizzing them. bd
